                        "content": "The nurse is monitoring the respiratory status of a client with laryngeal cancer after creation of a tracheostomy. Which coexisting condition in the client may cause an inaccurate pulse oximetry reading?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHypotension, shock, or the use of peripheral vasoconstricting medications may result in inaccurate pulse oximetry readings as a result of impaired peripheral perfusion. Fever and epilepsy would not affect the accuracy of measurement. Respiratory failure also would not affect the accuracy of measurement, although the readings may be abnormally low.",
                        "id": "102f2627d9c440709e5e09e85f8d75cf",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
