                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client suspected of having lung cancer after a bronchoscopy and biopsy. Which finding, if noted in the client, would be reported immediately to the primary health care provider?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIf a biopsy was performed during a bronchoscopy, blood-streaked sputum is expected for several hours. Frank blood indicates hemorrhage. A dry cough may be expected. The client needs to be assessed for signs of complications, which would include cyanosis, dyspnea, stridor, bronchospasm, hemoptysis, hypotension, tachycardia, and dysrhythmias. Hematuria is unrelated to this procedure.",
                        "id": "1e64896e09294355b3c94988c3a72430",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "254f1ae14af690d69d154586cd2487b1",
                                "content": "Pleural friction rub"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a311c46b1ed844e4c53ed72885cd29b4",
                                "content": "Vesicular breath sounds"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "72acdd9c59ecef9a38f5f1625b1826fd",
                                "content": "Bronchial breath sounds"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "c8d91b5be5bee7fde4396f802f582f9b",
                                "content": "Bronchovesicular breath sounds"
                            }
