                        "content": "The client is returned to the nursing unit following thoracic surgery to treat lung cancer with a chest tube in place. During the first few hours postoperatively, the nurse assesses for drainage and expects to note which characteristics?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIn the first few hours after surgery the drainage from the chest tube is bloody. After several hours it becomes serosanguineous. The client would not experience frequent clotting. Proper chest tube function would allow for drainage of blood before it has the chance to clot in the chest or the tubing.",
                        "id": "4fef608dc5e94590ba3c8efaf47d4582",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
